news.title: China Evergrande Group resumes work on pre-sold projects
news.para: Evergrande, which has been scrambling to raise funds it needs to pay its many lenders and suppliers, said it will continue to engage with its offshore creditors and hopes to reach a consensus on the terms of a restructuring plan.

news.title: China: CIFI Holdings, Agile Group to raise funds via discounted share sales
news.para: Shanghai-based CIFI, which is undergoing an offshore debt restructuring, said it would raise HK$957.6 million ($123 million) by selling shares at HK$1.14 apiece, a 14% discount to Monday's closing price.

news.title: Jaipur development body to take loan on behalf of JMRC for extension of metro
news.para: On November 21, 2022, the finance department gave clearance for construction of Line 1C of Jaipur Metro. This extension would connect a 2.26 km stretch from Badi to Transport Nagar on the Delhi-Agra Highway.

news.title: Lucknow: No houses for allottees of Rohtas Plumeria homes' P tower even after a decade
news.para: Presently, 14 projects are being rehabilitated through either the promoters or the AOA in UP. RPH is the first project under rehabilitation program in Lucknow, where pending projects will be commercialized by builder to complete it.

news.title: The great Bengaluru house hunt: Tenants in despair as rents go north
news.para: While eviction notices are being served under the pretext of rent increase, many are jostling to find a stay at an affordable rate.

news.title: Lucknow development body seals illegal plotting, row houses
news.para: ​​Anti-encroachment drive was launched on the directive of LDA vice-chairman Indramani Tripathi. Devansh Trivedi, enforcement officer of zone 2, said the LDA team sealed illegal plotting in a township of a prominent builder.

news.title: Ludhiana: Civic officials plan new site for construction waste utilisation plant
news.para: However, this highlights poor planning among civic officials. Earlier the carcass utilization plant in Noorpur village could not be utilised till date because of protest by villagers.

news.title: Deadlock on closure of cement plants in Himachal Pradesh continues as talks remain inconclusive
news.para: In the statement issued to the media on Tuesday, Adani group has stated that it is deeply aggrieved with the situation caused by the adamant stand of the truck unions in Himachal Pradesh.

news.title: Ranchi's deputy mayor writes to government over building regularisation
news.para: ​Vijayvargiya said his proposal was submitted as part of the government’s efforts to legalise unapproved structures. A couple of weeks ago, the government announced to regularise such buildings with a one-time payment.

news.title: Residents want Bengaluru civic body to take over KHB Layout
news.para: Most of the roads in the layout are either riddled with potholes or are muddy. The layout’s lifeline— a road connecting it to Kengeri — is used by many school buses and is choked every day.

news.title: Over 14 lakh families await PMAY-Gramin houses in Odisha
news.para: More than 14 lakh out of the 32.36 lakh eligible families in the state are waiting to get houses under the Pradhan Mantri Awaas Yojana-Gramin (PMAY-G), Union minister of state for rural development Sadhvi Niranjan Jyoti stated in Lok Sabha on Tuesday.The 32.

news.title: Geo-mapping being used to identify unauthorised constructions in Patna: Centre tells SC
news.para: ​The apex court was hearing a plea filed by Patna resident Ashok Kumar Sinha against June 30, 2020 order of the National Green Tribunal (NGT) dismissing his petition against illegal constructions and permanent encroachments on the floodplain.

news.title: Kolhapur: Urban development department allows revised building plan submissions offline
news.para: The Kolhapur Municipal Corporation (KMC) and Kolhapur Urban Development Authority (KUDA) have received a circular from the UD department in this regard.

news.title: Three-bedroom flat in Chandigarh sector 63 fetches Rs 1.5 crore in auction
news.para: Two other three-bedroom units in Sector 63 were sold for Rs 1.47 crore and Rs 1.38 crore against the same reserve price of Rs 1.12 crore. A total of 167 properties, both commercial and residential, were up for auction.

news.title: Kolkata: Bowbazar rebuild plan gets one bidder, families fear delay
news.para: A KMRC official had told TOI in October they wanted to start work by February 2023 so that the first lot of families could move in in 2025.
